ascents.name: Stained Glass
ascents.comment: Oh wow! First post break accent?? You’ll have to excuse Gregor, he’s a little weak! Improbable send after feeling horrible and so gassy. Just here to maintain my #1 spot on the 30 day crag rank. Ooo shalaylay

ascents.name: Center Direct
ascents.comment: I just want to shoutout Matteo and Ryan for giving me the tools to always be bicycling (ABB) and drop off with style. Felt somewhere between orange and purple tag. Right hand blew on the jump to the jug so took the one arm swing and luckily caught the foot before peeling off. Psyched to do a solid double d

ascents.name: Ex-patriot
ascents.comment: This is the one you want. Hell it's the one I wanted for a long time. Shout out to all who went with me to this boulder and watched me fail time and again. And shoutout to the homies that padded  this up today. It's been a long time comin'.

ascents.name: Greenpeace Sit
ascents.comment: Long live Shirley!

ascents.name: Twin Cracks
ascents.comment: i'm not gonna call this soft at least not as soft as drone direct one move in. the perfect comment! thumbs up!

ascents.name: Power Of Geometry
ascents.comment: Send train with Davey. Nice consolation prize after not being able to do giving tree for a 4th consecutive year. Ah well, maybe 2020

ascents.name: Soul Shine
ascents.comment: This climb might be more accurately termed the Right Road Right Exit. Do first two moves of Right Road to get Left hand slot, right hand same height edge, heel corner of arete, deadpoint to edge below jug of soul shine, bump to jug. Feels way easier than today’s standard method and climbs much better as well. Would DG to 8 but whatever. I still want to have friends

ascents.name: Cobra Con
ascents.comment: It’s Kobra Kon in the book. I don’t even know if that’s the correct spelling. Anyway, definitely sickest boulder I’ve done here. May not do a boulder as nice as this the rest of the trip.

ascents.name: Swanky Sit
ascents.comment: This thing is just way too many moves. Came in thinking it would be easy because fresh feelings. But that was Hubris speaking and he’s a total dick. 12 moves is like 4 boulder problems so maybe this is more like 5.12b. Clipped the chains and it was total limit. Ooo shalaylay

ascents.name: Finders fee
ascents.comment: M-flash babyyy! Sorry Gregor, grasping at straws is unsanitary and doesn't make you better at crimping. Happy bday Drew. You are a sillybilly. stay well-odored and strength you sweetboi

ascents.name: Michael Caine
ascents.comment: Shouts out to K dizzle aka Kody Dolla, aka Shutt tha Dude! You know what it is

ascents.name: Last Dance
ascents.comment: after like 6 sessions of falling I realized that this thing is probably not v8. climbed it the og way no crazy high heel, and double clutched the jug. feels good to finally bag.

ascents.name: One Mule Wonder
ascents.comment: probably more like V8 but if it's good enough for Fanny it's good enough for me.

ascents.name: Twilight of the Idols
ascents.comment: Maybe 7 goes total? Incredible rock climb. Fun moves, nice height, and perrty. Felt leagues easier than Ex-pat and honestly, I can see this being low end V8 so i'll split the difference here.

ascents.name: Pugilist
ascents.comment: Cool moves. Very soft. Other Millie had a very unfortunate series of events happen to her and they just kept coming. At least we made it home.

ascents.name: Solar Power SDS
ascents.comment: Maybe like soft 7 into the stand which is basically soft 7. Questionable but I’ll take the points. Psyched Natey pulled the stand. My spotting is leveling up!

ascents.name: Soul Caliber
ascents.comment: Took a few goes to remember I was born with balls and should use them. Psyched! On another note, I realized while hiking that I’ve never been to undiscovered country without David. So my approach to this was: walk to Wonderbug, bushwack uphill, think I’m too high, go back down a ways, miraculously stumble upon black cauldron, think I’m good now, wander for 20 minutes before I find Ebonic Woman, then wander another 20 minutes and realize I’m at My Infested, give up. Get lost on the way back to my pads at Ebonic and find it. I think I get it now

ascents.name: Byron's Roof
ascents.comment: This thing still felt pretty hard. Def felt harder than right road. My 21 move circle boulder on the 45 has given me the tools to be own boss. And not fall post crux. And that’s certainly meaningful cha feel?

ascents.name: The Right Road
ascents.comment: 3rd solo session to tram and it didn’t disappoint. I did five boulders. But still can’t do mutiny so I still suck. I just want to take a moment and give a quick shoutsout to Frankie Oceeeean. Not the man himself but the Spotify playlist of his bangers I made and titled as previously mentioned. Crack rock got me up every boulder I did!

ascents.name: Caramel Sutra
ascents.comment: Barely eked this one out. Given that, in addition to the boulder suiting my only true climbing talent which is high ledge feet and pimping those crystals, it seems legit. Dumpy boulders are all I have on these days.

ascents.name: Year of the Cat
ascents.comment: somewhere between soft and not soft 9. Fun one mover still hate the stand. Just need skin and this season is on!!

ascents.name: Left Hand of Darkness
ascents.comment: at long last. This one was quite the epic. Probably real close to redlining but finally pulled this testpiece. I can't really think of a climb that suits my style so well that I found so difficult to finish. But hey, frustratingly out of reach until I did it then it was soft. If it wasn't for David's shitty V8 mantel FA in the valley, which is probably V7 anyway, I'd be spanking him by a whole soft second go. ah well. at least I didn't lay a goose egg today. or really any other egg because most eggs just look like the number 0.

ascents.name: Champagne arete
ascents.comment:
Aka the KBMSA problem. Would give V8 but kody still hasn't done this. It was baking in the sun and I lost two tips to fat holes and still pulled. Kody.

KODY!

ascents.name: Out Of Your League
ascents.comment: Well it took exactly 10 months and like 4 dg's but finally bagged a climb I feel comfortable calling harder than 7B+. Top was a little sketch but I harnessed my inner Davey and fell upwards on it.

ascents.name: Soul Slinger
ascents.comment: This boulder problem is soft. No doubt. Felt like V7 when I sent. But, it took me so long to figure out the subtleties and dial everything in. Anyway, I finally broke the barrier into V9. I was pretty close on a few others throughout 2016 but alas they did not go. 2017 will be the deciding year for Alan Nalitch. I can feel it in my ass.

ascents.name: Monkey Bar Direct
ascents.comment: finally. Swore off the jump beta but just did it anyway. Maybe i'm making my way out of this valley after all

ascents.name: Saigon Direct
ascents.comment: I really want to give this 7 and make it my 91st on my road to 100 (flex) but I won’t. Definitely not V9 but I am a chronic downgrader (also flex) maybe this will kickstart my journey to 100 V8s (more than halfway there (flex))

ascents.name: Overzealous
ascents.comment: Another @kshutt11 inspired boulder in which all of the holds face the same way. Didn’t toe hook at all just used the feet on the face. Felt somewhat like a much easier version of Michael Caine.

ascents.name: Bush pilot
ascents.comment: What a wonderful wonderful move to be able to do with your friends and all the other people in the world and I know that I can do it all right now and then I’ll try to find out what I was doing today

ascents.name: Sombrero
ascents.comment: I am quite bad at this sort of thing. Felt preeetty hard to me. First cold days of the season hooray!

ascents.name: Science Friction
ascents.comment: This is a nice rock climb. I used the jug out left because why would I not use it? Probably V6 for the reachers, but I am not a reachy boy.

ascents.name: Hop Scotch
ascents.comment: andyliu84 was right about this one...but I need the pointzzzz

ascents.name: Attack of the Staph
ascents.comment: M flash babyyy. Stiffest 6 this side of the Mississippi (besides Ak’s (but only if you round up))

ascents.name: Barefoot Sharma Arete
ascents.comment: AK did this too. And I’m not surprised because he climbs V9 in the gym

ascents.name: Heel-a-Peel
ascents.comment: movement actually isn't that bad. but it's a dumpy boulder and very very bad bad. Also so easy. psyched on the choss!

ascents.name: Soul Snatch
ascents.comment: This was definitely not Soul Snatch

ascents.name: The Drill Sergeant
ascents.comment: kinda shitty but also fun. but also pretty funny looking.

ascents.name: Pimpsqueak
ascents.comment: Damnit why didn't I just bump the right hand 8 inches higher? Quite a nice rock climb. Surprised I did it so quickly given how over rock climbing I was. ooo shalaylay

ascents.name: Fridge Left
ascents.comment: fuck this one was fucked up. did this weird mantel and then slapped to crimp from the mantle. still don't know if it's mantel or mantle.

ascents.name: Cocktail sauce
ascents.comment: so psyched to do cocktail saucev10. everyone must know, the world will know!

ascents.name: Croft Problem
ascents.comment: moves quite well actually for a humpty dumpty climb. Like popping a tire but having a full spare. except we didn't have a spare tire at all this weekend. and sad we were about that.

ascents.name: Ten Pin trial
ascents.comment: gaston'ed the pinch with the left hand and locked off to the jug edge. Sequence by itself felt about V8 but i guess adding a V4 doesn't really add a grade. Psyched to have a volume day out in the milks with KBMS and the Marlens.

ascents.name: Junior's achievement
ascents.comment: This is very nice. Tried it 4 years ago or so and had no real business being on it. Psyched to do it quickly this time around

ascents.name: Strawberry Contraceptives Left
ascents.comment: Kody falling on the second move got me v psyched to give it a go. Double gastons are the light of my life. Kody please add 'Planet X' to sector so that we show up together.

ascents.name: Lost and Found
ascents.comment: i just want to shout out kody, zev, chris, david, and nick all of whom, as fate would have it, are some of my favorite strongboiz, for cleaning off the choss with their 8a comments. i felt very fine topping out this tp. very much my style so probably not soft. hooray.

ascents.name: Arbor Day sds
ascents.comment: so good. very fun movement on a cool looking boulder. Somehow managed to bag a boulder with 10+ moves so it must be soft. just kidding. Probably solid 7 just to get into the stand.

ascents.name: Sword of Damocles
ascents.comment: Highball grades baby! Bottom is hard and a bit miserable but the rest is pretty much incredible. Nice to slay boulders with the senderstrongboiz KBMS and MHFL. Davy baby we'll be back next week for you to croosh.

ascents.name: Brian's Project
ascents.comment: the anti-style goes! Shoe came halfway off on the send go, had to hammer my foot into the rock to put the heel back in. just me and my #podboiz out here wildin'

ascents.name: Nothing But Sunshine
ascents.comment: calling a spade a spade here. every hold is jug. Moves very well and is very much my style. soft that is.

ascents.name: Vulgarine
ascents.comment: This is a very good boulder problem. Not super striking but moves exceptionally well  and is actually kinda tall when it's said and done. Suits my style perfectly and still felt hard. Soft Second go just rolls off the tongue better than just second go. Worth doing.

ascents.name: Velvet Revolver Sit
ascents.comment: The full line is quite nice. First move always felt hard before but was ez today. Fun day with a different crew than i'm used to. I might not go to wild things without you Davey. But I also might. i'd hurry if i were you.

ascents.name: Moonraker
ascents.comment: fun moves. Daniel is the only one to give this V7 out of 244 ascents and I'm the one who gets shit for downgrading. having said that, if one's lower body weighs 3x as much as their upper body, that swing is for real. Thank god for steel cable tendons and Daniel's sandbag or I might not have called this soft.

ascents.name: Lululator Low
ascents.comment: If you're the type of sendbro that walks up to the slightly overhanging section of your local climbing gym, glosses over all of the handholds, and dials in on the foot jibs, you are in LUCK! Only have two fingers on each hand? No problem! None of the holds need more than that! So come on down, grab a pad and pimp these crystal jibs.

ascents.name: Midnight Lightning
ascents.comment: At long last. Wonderful movement all around. If mantel was four feet off the ground it would be a kind of weird V2. Fall temps are here!

ascents.name: Fear and Loathing in Tuolumne
ascents.comment: Same grade as Lost but Not Forgotten. Psyched this felt ez this time around.

ascents.name: Vanishing Point
ascents.comment: M soft second go. After doing everything else, I thought maybe this would feel soft despite the sketch. Turns out...I was right! I’ve never even been to Mount San Jacinto

ascents.name: Green Peace
ascents.comment: m-soft second go hooray. I will be back asap for the sit.

ascents.name: Lohbo
ascents.comment: Took way longer than it should have. high heel cross right to jug pinch, jahmp out to jug. Forgot how to top it out. Had to do it all again. getting back in shape but black was already too hot today.

ascents.name: Yogi variation
ascents.comment: At least this one tops out. Had to really fight for this one. Another anti-steeze victory in the books. So much climbing. Today was a little foreshadow into how summer is going to go with Lil ib who savagely flashes V6's and downgrades them to V4. You can beg and plead but it's still V4 to Lil ib. Don't get offended he was just giving you hard time. Maybe you tried at the wrong time.

ascents.name: Checkerboard
ascents.comment: Finally! So good! I need crimps 16 of 'em.

ascents.name: Olde Glory
ascents.comment: There's just something about the rock quality here at drug dome/mariolumne that makes it so nice. solid bullet granite for sure if you ask me. ask chris.

ascents.name: Megalomania
ascents.comment: soft third go after sticking first move aka stgasfm. Bummer we couldn't find born under punches drew. this will have to do.

ascents.name: The 8th Dimension
ascents.comment: Very psyched. Punted super hard off the top on the mantel after being pressed out for like two minutes straight. holy isht that ish is hard. I love toehooks now that my #madrocklvdrones aka the skinny skates have so much toe rubber. shoutout sportiva for being cool with me using the drones to send my proj.

ascents.name: Loh roof
ascents.comment: i gotta stop warming up on things at my max. Topout was ez, just kind of unenjoyable.

ascents.name: Gluttony
ascents.comment:
Topped out in the rain with an LIB type spotding me. Nothing tastes as good as being thin feels...Except Roscoe's and Thai Chili.

and steak and pizza and milkshakes and cookies and...

ascents.name: Matt Hoch Problem
ascents.comment: Should have just ticked the jug at the lip for the flash go. Was just left of it! Having said that, this thing is a movement masterpiece. As if our lord and savior jesus christ air made it just for me.

ascents.name: Worst Case Scenario
ascents.comment: M-frash. Tried it earlier in the trip when pretty tired and didn't come close. Tried it on the last day when completely wrecked and sent. So weird.

ascents.name: Lightning
ascents.comment: Cool problem. good movement. don't know if just my style but felt really easy even in sun. hike from parking lot to trailside boulder is actually pretty heinous. god i'm so out of shape. so embarrassing.

ascents.name: Thin Lizzy
ascents.comment: Holy soft. handful of goes. pretty much locked off the first move. "Ultralight Girthv6" at the UCLA rockwall is much harder.

ascents.name: Acid Wash right
ascents.comment: i'll give this the qualified soft 7B+. I can now finally say that I'm as strong as Nathaniel. Yes. Great rock climber.

ascents.name: The Diamond
ascents.comment: First valley V8. The epic is over. Probably spent 4-5 sessions on this thing. This session I got to the last move 4 times, hit the jug and punted the 5th, and sent the 6th. Was sick to get a send train going with David, Daniel Fineman, and myself. That's a good group. This is the only thing I did all weekend. But I've learned I just have to knockout everything I've tee'd up one boulder at a time. And I think that's more meaningful.

ascents.name: Lost, But not forgotten
ascents.comment: Oh my heinous dab. Mega hit the upright pad with my foot on the send go but it was after latching the jug so just...give it to me?? Whatever, business hours are over baaaabyyy! Classic me with the pogo ftw.

ascents.name: Jedi Monkey
ascents.comment: 2.5 stars because it is contrived. Very fun movement though on great rock. Wrist exploded on solar power sit the day prior in addition to slicing my finger open, so this felt pretty hard. But its soft. And thats

ascents.name: Little Wing
ascents.comment: Used the jug to the right as a foot. Could def be even easier than 8 but whatever. A more difficult version of Planet of the Apes. Definitely need bigger biceps to do it proper style. But we're just out here training for real rock climbing.

ascents.name: A Fragile Term
ascents.comment: This boulder was meant to be climbed by a fat asian boy with a shitty shitty body. After due consideration I have elected...not to not downgrade. Will def come back to do the sitter which should clock in around 9 or 10.

ascents.name: Fly Boy Sit
ascents.comment: First time ever coming to bishop two years ago, I couldnt climb V2 but sherpa'd pads to this boulder for the ucla rockwall legends and wanted to do it ever since. Msoft2ndGO-led the charge with Davey, and Ryan following with their hyper-athletic jumping straight for jug method. Wish rock climbing was more of a skill sport but what can you do? Good times with great people. Shoutout Scott for driving and not getting injured, and jax for finally putting down her nemesis!

ascents.name: Solitaire
ascents.comment: I've been queued up for quite some time. Psyched first of grade is this rad boulder! Coolest fucking move on the planet!!

ascents.name: Lobsters and Also Their Balls
ascents.comment: I don't know the name, nor do I know if this was ever given one. So this is just a place holder that, as time passes, will overtake any previously given name. Located on the smooth shrimp boulder, left of the mega jug warm up/downclimb, started crossed on pancreas-high holds and used mostly tears but also crimps to climb into those mega jugs. Scott said he tried it and that it was fucked up. But I did it, Scott. I did it man

ascents.name: Water Hazard right
ascents.comment: My 100th V7 and how fitting that it is  one star and double-dged. On to 100 V8s (flex)

ascents.name: Monkey Bar Traverse
ascents.comment: Good god. five session-msoft second GO. Might be the new classic way to do boulders. God i suck at climbing at red rocks. on a brighter note, this is my 99th V7. On a less bright note, I couldn't get to a hundo this trip. On a brighter note, bishop still has some lowball choss for me to do to get there

ascents.name: The Dirty Rail
ascents.comment: Actually quite a good one. completely whiffed on the second move, was granted a mulligan, and mulligan flashed which is not necessarily the same as an m-flash

ascents.name: My Tan
ascents.comment: My style and still felt pretty hard. Much easier than bubble butt and Mr. Moran I'm pretty sure

ascents.name: Bubble Butt
ascents.comment: pretty hard for a boi so soft as me. Much more difficult than my tan

ascents.name: Mr. Moran
ascents.comment: The epitome of why I suck at red rocks. Everyone thinks this is easy but i couldn't link any moves and then somehow Fanny'd it. Happy bday to me

ascents.name: The Corner SDS
ascents.comment: actually decently fun. And it's also another V7 which is nice. Seems easier than power glide but whatever. Ak i'm sorry that we couldn't hang this weekend. i still luv u and i hope u still luv me too

ascents.name: Spittin' Venom
ascents.comment: 3 goes. Extremely easy. Did not flash or soft second go because I was v tired and precision was off. Otherwise, probably a pretty accessible first V7 for most

ascents.name: The Penthouse
ascents.comment: Actually quite good. The Estate Tax project is also quite good and I nearly came away with the FA. But alas, I am still deep in a valley of my own despair

ascents.name: Pope's Roof
ascents.comment: i climbed yesterday but david.vaskos.com says I didn't. how do we rectify this, admin? I am not good at rock climbing in this current moment

ascents.name: Igneous Ambiance
ascents.comment: Oh wow I did not think of the flashing but I doing it and on the top wow! Congratulated!!

ascents.name: Mulligan Variation
ascents.comment: I am bumming because the start holds. What is it about the technical?? Should be flashing but because start holds Igneous I never could? Shucks!!

ascents.name: All Washed Up
ascents.comment: So hard. Could be V8. Wow my softness rating, my poor softness rating!!

ascents.name: Pumping monzonite
ascents.comment: Really shucking up my softness rating today

ascents.name: Unnamed
ascents.comment: To the right of the problem to the right of nothin' but sunshine. Kody thinks this is V9 but that's not what other folks are saying. And that's not his fault, he shirley would have heard the rumors if he could hear out of his right ear. Anyway, start left hand on small incut sidepull, right hand on bad pinch bump right hand a few times to pinches and slopers, top out and add to the softness rating baby!

ascents.name: Mutiny
ascents.comment: This one has been haunting me for the worse part of a decade. All I had to do was cross to the nothing sloper and pimp those crystals. I should have known. The sea of green gods smile upon me on this day.

ascents.name: A boy named Sue
ascents.comment: Ah yes what a nice rock climb. The sit is soft but harder than my life so I must come back for it

ascents.name: Unitizing the G
ascents.comment: One of my two v7’s that I bagged today! The first is this one and the second is a different one. Also bagged a long standing project from my last time I was in Tramway a couple months ago

ascents.name: A Tribe Called Conquest Direct
ascents.comment: This is a big big boy with a few big big falls from boys. Finally, after several seasons of not committing, all I had to do was jump to the last hold! I’m sorry we couldn’t send together, Gregor, but maybe the other Gregor here is right. Maybe it is V11 and I have at last made my entrance into sidebar territory? No. No most certainly not.

ascents.name: Not a Flowmaster
ascents.comment: To the left of Tetrys. I have no idea what I did here. Started as low as I could with two crimps, left heel, hit horrible crimp left hand, cranked heel, bumped into gaston, cranked heel, backflagged and desperately slapped right hand into arete, left hand to bucket crimp. Felt about 7 to me but may have done a horrible sequence. What the fuck is a sideshelf mountain project? Jesus.

ascents.name: Itsy Bitsy Spider Right
ascents.comment: very soft and lovely.

ascents.name: Tour de France Arete Sit
ascents.comment: This thing is so miserable. Horrible rock climb

ascents.name: Thin Face sit
ascents.comment: ehh climbing was ok. into the stand. not super great though.

ascents.name: Hesitation Factor
ascents.comment: this is very very fun fun and sweet sweet potato pie. power crimping at it's finest. Ak took some fat whips on this boi

ascents.name: House Kung Fu
ascents.comment: very nice boulder problem. cool pogo-esque thingy. I thought this was probably a bit hard for 6 and what do you know? Thank you based climbing community for keeping it soft.

ascents.name: Four-Fifths Face
ascents.comment: This was total limit, Mark P! Horrible feet and good yet very small crimps. Cut feet like an idiot on move 2 and sold my soul to stay on. Pogo'd the last move and clipped the chainz. I've done it!

ascents.name: Junk In A Box
ascents.comment: 2nd go. Book description says one hard move to a pinch and finish up the V1 topout. But the move to the pinch was super easy and there was no mention of the second and much harder move. this was nice and soft.

ascents.name: Mimosa
ascents.comment: also did not use the undercling tooth because it's stupid. right hand on sidepull edge, left hand on nothing, heel and magic!

ascents.name: Grotesque old woman
ascents.comment: I was told that this was what I wanted by @vasko6d via Bezosbudz direct messaging. Hard until i did it but really it was just soft all along.

ascents.name: Tin Man Sit
ascents.comment: chugged 3 beers before this so it was a pleasant surprise. bummed i don't get to log book no score the stand.

ascents.name: Raging Bull
ascents.comment: not sure when i did this but i did and it's high time i start my journey to 100 7's. hoorah

ascents.name: Busted
ascents.comment: i'd like to say that I once again soft-second go'd an 8 but this was just so incredibly soft that there is no shot in dodge. my guy

ascents.name: The Shield
ascents.comment: took a few goes. apparently it broke and now it's harder? idk david couldn't repeat it and Kenny couldn't do it so that doesn't make much sense. soft

ascents.name: The Flake
ascents.comment: msoft second GO! This climb is like fly boy arete in that if you don't have buffer grades it's going to feel like terrible movement. All of the holds face the same way and who actually likes that?? Anyways it's a nice rock climb and worth doing. You're welcome Kody.

ascents.name: Unnamed
ascents.comment: to the left of croft problem. not that bad once the betas is rights. felt very soft but also I may not have a clue what anything is gradewise anymore.

ascents.name: Flight Attendant
ascents.comment: If it wasn't for the rock and the hollow sounding crimps that you have to pimp, this would be a really good climb. Kody remember when you said that you'd never doubt me again? When will you ever learn...

ascents.name: *Rave
ascents.comment: I wish there was an intermediate level sidebar that only weak bois like me could be featured on. Maybe in 8b.nu Jensybaby. Probably top 3 hardest V7’s I’ve ever done. Maybe it’s just because of my oversized jumbos.

ascents.name: Strawberry Contraceptives
ascents.comment: kind of unenjoyable actually. went straight into undercling and matched gross. also pulled an Ak at the top and groveled upwards. should have crossed to the crimp on the fraish go. boo!

ascents.name: Pow Pow
ascents.comment: felt very impossible due to sliding on zero skin. Then I realized I just had to rock climb it and it went v easy. Last time I tried this I gave it maybe 4 attempts and dry heaved behind the boulder in between those attempts. Shoutout jim beam

ascents.name: Red Rum
ascents.comment: another nemesis down. this is in the running for hardest v7 ever. i can wait to do the sit. it's fine.

ascents.name: The Peanut
ascents.comment: for sure hardest thing I did on this day. That right hand edge just did not feel ergonomic at all. Took way more goes than Nothing but Sunshine. Weird

ascents.name: Resonator
ascents.comment: first 7 flash. Couldn't have been more my style. Not too bad just gotta be able to pimp those crystals which I do. And even if I didn't, which I do. Then this thing could be considered soft which it is.

ascents.name: Poop Shoot
ascents.comment: ehh this climb kinda sucks. super dabby and like goes on forever. but the pointz baby! and the sea of green.

ascents.name: Lip Service
ascents.comment: Almost blew the top. honestly almost blew the whole thing. when you got splits and can't crimp, trailside boulder is your friend. guess i'll be back for Shoot the Moon and Joy

ascents.name: Salty Spittoon
ascents.comment: God this thing is a real piece of work. ultra dabby and covered in cum, you'd think that'd be enough. But then that topout goes and....completely ruins it!! My wrist does not feel good. underclings above one's head are super dumb always. soft.

ascents.name: Get Carter
ascents.comment: Just needed 3 buffer grades to bag it. Bishop is hot. i am le tired.

ascents.name: Chadinator
ascents.comment: Movement wise actually pretty good. but wow my eyeholes burn.

ascents.name: Left Left Gold Crack Sit
ascents.comment: cool moves. felt hard for me. soft

ascents.name: Tramslot Traverse
ascents.comment: Running out of good 7 and unders to do at the Tramway. At least this one moves somewhat well.

ascents.name: Midnight Train
ascents.comment: Best thing done this weekend. This wall is sweet as!! Sandbox crew rolled strong thanks to our gracious host, Sarah DJ. Shoutout you.

ascents.name: Evan and Amy
ascents.comment: nice little boulder. V7 seemed fair to me too. Scott with the skivvy send. it is now too hot to climb in CA

ascents.name: Tin can alley
ascents.comment: Dang the coldstream area has some pretty fun boulders! weird moves and odd body positions  and a big ol' scott barron smackdown. chee huu

ascents.name: The Splinter
ascents.comment: In fairness, I believe trains have engines at both the front and back, powering the heavy, heavy cargo in the middle. Anyway, this climb is very nice. Comparable in difficulty and spiciness to Butterscotch so low end 7A+ seems fair.Interesting movement and holds, tall and pretty. 3 more sends today means the top is even cleaner. Go get it people!

ascents.name: Inside Out
ascents.comment: This climb has wonderful movement. Not dabby if you can crimp but you can't David so your comment has some merit. 'craters of the moon' however, has no merit at all. i hope one day you realize that

ascents.name: Angry Beaver
ascents.comment: Hey is this the crush beavers party?

ascents.name: Austin Powers
ascents.comment:
One move wonder into jerg crimps. Very annoying how precise one must be on such a big move but satisfying when i bagged!

Anyway. Solo trip to black was sack and in Classic Shirley fashion. I forgot my shit everywhere and had to go search for it, I thought I forgot my shit and searched everywhere only to find my shit was in my chalkbag the whole time, vag split both my index fingers, highballed with two napkins and no spot, circled a Up Up and away like three times because I thought I was lost and there was no way that there was actually a boulder problem in this mini-talus, found it only to see that it broke and is way too hard now, oh and Millie made it there and back like the stud that she is!! I love my Millie!

ascents.name: Caveman
ascents.comment: 1.5 stars for cool movement. Sequence is quite intricate. But it's a drop off so. Anyway this was the anti-steez redemption day and I'll take the W for this one.

ascents.name: Pain Grain sit
ascents.comment: Took me about three seshy's to rediscover the crimp. And that only really happened because david ran up there and pointed at it. Cool boulder. quite soft but i'll take it.

ascents.name: Terra Firma Cosmonaut
ascents.comment: Although the window of opportunity is absurdly short every year, you can't sit back on your keister when destiny comes knocking. You just gotta go. That's what Je-- Tess-- Terra Firma, rather... taught me.

ascents.name: Dead Space
ascents.comment: Probably definitely would have flashed if I had that softy beta. Taking the points for my broken body. When does climbing get easier?

ascents.name: Freedom Fighter sit
ascents.comment: Sit adds like a 3 move boulder problem that might be considered V5. Idk. I was tired but it felt really easy still. I'll come through with a 7 bar. just for the bitches.

ascents.name: The Carapace
ascents.comment: nice HP40 esque climb. Never been to HP40. Don't know where it is or what the boulders look like. But they sound soft. Erik Christensen is my dude. Never met Erik Christensen. Don't know who he is or what he looks like but he sounds like a sweet boy.

ascents.name: Wildcat
ascents.comment: Almost flashed then proceeded to fall on the last move for 2 sessions. V5 into the last V4 move clocks in around 6. But I want the pointz baby! Good warm up for not sending Ex Pat.

ascents.name: Lion's Mane
ascents.comment: soft third go really doesn't have the same ring to it. looked at this thing a couple years ago and thought it looked heinous. ended up using the wrong hold on the flash, then foot pick on the soft second go. Psyched I can still pull 7's running on donuts and fried chicken.

ascents.name: Compression Matters
ascents.comment:
anywhere from 4 to 7 depending on how much of a bitch you are.

oh wait shit. wait hold on i didn't mean--

ascents.name: Born Under Punches
ascents.comment: Natebro actually punted twice. And then couldn't do the easiest move in iso. He put up a fat goose egg. But Natebro always pulls.

ascents.name: Vegan Shoveler
ascents.comment: Also kind of uncomfortable for sure. but the arete climbing is wellworth it. can't believe it took David 3 sessions to bag. sachi!

ascents.name: Velvet Revolver
ascents.comment: This thing is somehow really hard. for sure not V6. David Vasko. One day i'll be able to try hard like davey but for now...i'm sad to say that this is not soft and i will be back for the soft sit.

ascents.name: Tour De France
ascents.comment: Felt so much better than two years ago. softest of the trip 7 today after just flailing everywhere for over a month. Winter is coming.

ascents.name: Captain America
ascents.comment: Skin is real thin. Was basically sliding on every hold despite good temps.Hope this means my climing is on an upswing. I need a win, guys.

ascents.name: El Brute
ascents.comment: difficult for me because can't pinch. felt impossible til i sent then it was soft. takin the pointz. i needs 'em.

ascents.name: Adamantium
ascents.comment: msoft second go my fav. probably not soft for 7A+. 2 years ago Davey and I went to this boulder and could barely even pull on. I may have muffed the mflash by skipping too many holds, but it was still quite fitting to come back with David and send train.

ascents.name: Cracker Boy
ascents.comment: Very nice rock climb. This was the one thing I wanted to do on this heinous trip. Psyched to take it down. so tired. sent around 1am.

ascents.name: Swing Dance
ascents.comment: Those crimps went from feeling impossibly small two years ago to big ol' fat jugs now. msoft second go. Ran into some seriously weird people at this boulder. Relentlessly awkward. at least this was soft.

ascents.name: Suspended in Silence
ascents.comment: Post break. Apparently still incredible. Feel like V7 is certainly fair. Super fun trip with Ak, Matthias, and randomly running into a solo Kyle Williams. Awesome crew! Ak moo'd in his sleep, Matthias refused to eat at Las Palmas, and Kyle really wanted to show me drop knee beta for Get Carter after the pollen grains. I don't give a fuck about drop knees, Kyle!

ascents.name: Pocket Rocket
ascents.comment: Without a doubt, the single hardest move I have ever done.

ascents.name: *Big Joe
ascents.comment: Jugz. First day of trip, tried this line, cut feet on a gaston pinch and completely exploded my wrist. Also didn't help that I was already 3 days on. There is a valuable lesson to be learned here about resting. Still haven't quite grasped it yet.

ascents.name: Bring the Heatwole
ascents.comment: Let's address the elephant in the room here. I know this place where you only need four dollars and can get not one, but two mcgriddles.

ascents.name: Cindy Swank
ascents.comment: got to the last move on the flash go. then proceeded to get f'ed in the B for the next 6 burns. a little wind gave me enough friction to eek this thing out. the beginning of Ryan Bauer, 'The People's Champion' exhibition. what a show it was.

ascents.name: Jug Start to Acid Wash Right
ascents.comment: finally. so embarrassing.

ascents.name: Hand Grenade
ascents.comment: Oh my soft. Did it sans knee bar and was more than a few fireball handle pulls deep. Sick way to end a weird but hilarious weekend trip to Tooloom.

ascents.name: Thug Monkey
ascents.comment: 6 handlepulls, no warm up msoft4thgo'ed the last crosslink. Jax flashed G23 in style and Dustin followed up. Michael got his ass up Jedi Jake stand, first hard boulder post shoulder explosion. Sandbox went hard on this boulder as always.

ascents.name: Cellulite Eliminator
ascents.comment: First go from the sit. The stand felt so much easier after losing 15 lbs. Well I'm not surprised...

ascents.name: Over The Boardwalk
ascents.comment: Longest standing proj at Tramway taken down.Move felt so hard last year but cruised it this time despite greasiness. Left Hand will go next time. Just need to try it when it's cold. At this point, I am just about tee'd up everywhere in California.

ascents.name: 3am at denny's
ascents.comment: Oh my soft. Could even be 7A. I'm queued up here in Tahoe. Which is pretty much the worst thing ever. Shout out 2nd cop who came by apt 9 on that fateful evening some time ago. This one was for you.

ascents.name: Stand up
ascents.comment: Msoft second GO! Poor ryan destroyed all of his tips. Shoutout David, and Fineman. You took a while but you guys got up there!

ascents.name: Dark Continent
ascents.comment: Cool feature. Felt pretty hard, but Erik didn't do it. Soft.

ascents.name: Dirty Harry
ascents.comment: I was the only one who didn't flash or soft second go. May be easier if you're taller. Had to try so fucking hard.

ascents.name: No Holds Bard
ascents.comment: I'll give it the not soft for Fanny. When I first laid eyes on this boulder I knew I would love it: crimpy and high off the ground with a big ol' deadpoint crux at the top. Shoutout Konkey and all the #womenwhoboulder

ascents.name: Go Granny Ho
ascents.comment: mama i need chickuuuunss

ascents.name: High Plains Drifter
ascents.comment: WOW. perfect holds and movement. thing is 100% my style. felt pretty soft for 7. in b4 erik. one off the lifetime list. Could be a while before I get out here again. glad to put it down!

ascents.name: The King
ascents.comment:
points points points points points points points...


...yay

ascents.name: Jedi Jake
ascents.comment: The full line is awesome. felt like V5/6 to get into the stand. Surprised this went. Shirley Girth --> Slim Shirley? lewl. def not. I love full racks of ribs too much. Will be back for the crosslinks.

ascents.name: For the Glory
ascents.comment: Sorry Ryan, hope your rave was fun. almost perfect. kinda dirty and the huge rock in the landing zone. But tall, aesthetic, and moves so well.

ascents.name: Tommy's Arete
ascents.comment: This thing was awesome! perfect movement the whole way through. Just wish I did 4x4's before this trip. Really should have known better.

ascents.name: My Infested Destiny
ascents.comment: Amazing climb. An everything in one boulder. Heel hooks, slopers, crimps, jugs, spiciness, etc. #1 on my tram ticklist so psyched! Slimb will get his very soon!

ascents.name: Pit Boss
ascents.comment: Oh my greasy. Felt harder than fists of fury. Shoutout akhil for that inspirational pumpfake #throwbackgatorade!

ascents.name: Blue Flame
ascents.comment: Put seven sessions on it. redline was on the horizon. but shirley finally tried it when not tired and/or super fat. Soft.

ascents.name: Planet of the Apes
ascents.comment: Incredible movement, features, and holds.  Perfect compression on incut crimps and sloping jug rail to a full value mantle! Favorite send of the trip!

ascents.name: The Wind Below
ascents.comment: Holy PROUD king line. New beta is probably somewhere between 5 and 6 but gets the highball grade. Shirley knows a thing or two about high-steppin!

ascents.name: Picasso
ascents.comment: A few goes. had to find the soft beta for the bois quickly so that marina would not get lost. turns out only scott could do it (flex-assist) and Marina wasn't ever geographically lost (just had two left shoes) Very good rock climb

ascents.name: *Pearl Necklace
ascents.comment: Davey Davey Davey. You need some water in your life. You only eat plants. Plants only eat water. You need water by the transitive property of veggiebois

ascents.name: Power Glide
ascents.comment: couple o' goes. static'd the crux and my left hand was screaming. might be 7?

ascents.name: Snake oil
ascents.comment: Kody claims to have flashed this but honestly I doubt it. Someone complimented my core today which is currently made of jello so there's just a lot of dishonesty being thrown around here in 2020

ascents.name: French press
ascents.comment: so hard. but then when i did it, it was solid for the grade. At long last, i've done it. The V6 master list is complete. I am a Bishop V6 master! I can't do Molly Variation but trust me my loves, I've already mastered it

ascents.name: Molly Left Start
ascents.comment: holy shit. so many two finger pockets, mono's. So hard. Why is this not 7?

ascents.name: The One
ascents.comment: was trying way too low of a heel for like 7 burns until I realized that it didn't have to be V9 after all. Felt hard for me but I have accepted that my body is in a valley and these sorts of things happen. Another for the sea of green

ascents.name: Osama
ascents.comment: Such wonderful movement and so difficult. Felt like solid to hard V7 to me but perhaps I used the bad betas

ascents.name: DCD
ascents.comment: Chase can’t dyno either. Tried to double clutch so many times before realizing I am reachy enough to keep the foot. Thought this would be another 7 for 2019 but David thinks it’s soft 6. I’ll show you a soft 6, David!

ascents.name: Crimp Overhang
ascents.comment: Difficult first move but for sure my style. David you really missed out on a lovely cold and dry weekend with KBMS and the Lacavera boys. Don’t be a recluse please!

ascents.name: Tree Attack
ascents.comment:
shucks. can't give it more stars than david gave it and that's usually my modus operant conditioning. every softboi calls this hard but i won't. Does that make me a hard man? I think so...


I think so.

ascents.name: Burt's Butt
ascents.comment: so gross. why so many underclings? Like pulling on a sharty A. Flood climb on the 45.

ascents.name: Posse
ascents.comment: first go. nice move. then dumb campusing.

ascents.name: Beckey's Problem
ascents.comment: idk when i did this but i'm backlogging it because 100 V6's baby!!

ascents.name: Cruise control
ascents.comment: backlog. this was a decently good time.

ascents.name: The Hole
ascents.comment: yikes. this one hurt a little but i'm ok.

ascents.name: Smooth Shrimp
ascents.comment: 3 days at the milks means no acid wash Natebro. I'm really not worried about it at all to be honest. You've got a long way to go. I'll take my time.

ascents.name: The Cosmonaut
ascents.comment: hardest boulder in the valley. Summer of ShirLIB looking strong for 2019. Akhil, who regularly climbs v8 in the gym, has now downgraded two outdoor ones. C'mon Ak! do it for the summer of ShirLIB!

ascents.name: Howard Carter Sit Start
ascents.comment: apparently a hold broke but it didn't feel very hard still. Certainly not 7

ascents.name: Fly Boy
ascents.comment: pretty dumb but manageable way to get to the jump move. I am WRECKED.

ascents.name: Scatterbrain
ascents.comment: classic me missing the jug on the flash go. thank god for soft second GO!

ascents.name: Planet x
ascents.comment: An incredible rock climb. Didn't think the flash was that impressive until Austin and David spent an hour flailing on the jump move before bagging. Happy bday to me.

ascents.name: B1 Traverse SDS
ascents.comment: started left hand on sidepull down low, right hand on a nothing sloper on the arete. right hand to sloper dish on arete, left to tiny sidepull edge then jahmp into stand. Not sure if this is what was intended but felt like solid 6 to me.

ascents.name: Mr. Mackey
ascents.comment: sometimes you just have to imagine that you just climbed 10 feet of lovely V3 moves and then got to the start holds of this climb. Sometimes you also have to imagine there isn't a giant rock 8 inches away from where you are supposed to mantle (is it mantel or mantle i've never really known). I guess you have to imagine a lot for this climb to be good.

ascents.name: Pope's Prow
ascents.comment: psyched! felt impossible and got me totally gassed. so reachy but thank god mantel was super cashmere. Scott said to rock over there's nobody home, i rocked over there was nobody home! French Press is all that stands in my way now.

ascents.name: Dan Osman Arete
ascents.comment: bruh wtf. I will never be good at this kind of climbing ever. Awesome feature. only took me 5x more goes than everything else I did today. And to top it off, Davey has had a broken hand for like 3 months and still did this before me today. You'll always have the squeeze baby <3

ascents.name: DIB left
ascents.comment: Drew is bitch. Why didn't I just concur?

ascents.name: Green Wall Center
ascents.comment: another off the v6 master list. Just need Pope's Prow and French press to complete. Also this climb is kinda shitty. I did not really have fun on this. I guess it's cool to look at. soft.

ascents.name: Unknown
ascents.comment: Idk it was pretty fun and not that hard. Maybe my strength is leveling up? Nawwww

ascents.name: Unnamed
ascents.comment: Thought it was a 4 until Kody said it was a 6. Nom nom nom points

ascents.name: Stanage Problem
ascents.comment: short with pretty cool improbable mantel. psyched for the sea of green!

ascents.name: Malcomb
ascents.comment: i'll keep the grade for the 6-9 combo of the day. Solo trips are kinda cool but really they just suck. Everyone is injured. cry.

ascents.name: Poorman's Darkhorse
ascents.comment: dry fired on the move and fileted my pinky. boo hoo. almost blew the top but good thing I didn't ass flop on paul's cock until after this.

ascents.name: Memory Loss
ascents.comment: Ok i'm gonna put this whole 'Chase you need to stop downgrading' thing to rest right here because quite frankly i'm tired of it. Giant deadpoint to decent crimp first move is V6 by itself. There you go.

ascents.name: Cuticle Killer
ascents.comment: you can't just put it with your hands on it!

ascents.name: Girls on Film
ascents.comment: Classic big dick swingers calling this 6 in comments but still taking 7. Sweet as!

ascents.name: Little Country Girl
ascents.comment: Alright this one seemed kinda fucked up. But in retrospect, I'm pretty psyched taking down total choss moderates in a few goes no matter how I feel physically. It's like even if my ceiling isn't raising at all, at least my floor is improving from carpet to hardwood. savvy?

ascents.name: Milk the Milks
ascents.comment: 1st go got past the crux and missed a hold. Fell. Sharty. Now I have to climb this sharp shitty problem again. Next go, get to easy slab topout and spend 3 minutes convincing myself to switch feet on a jug. Not because of the fall, but because I really didn't want to climb this again.

ascents.name: Dusty Coffee Low
ascents.comment: Very uncomfortable but the hold was chalked and I really wanted some points real real bad. Is this a real thing? does it have another name? who knows! but it's soft. and that's guy fieri!

ascents.name: Vino Rojo
ascents.comment: After destroying myself in the gym for two days, and then destroying myself on the monkey bar boulders, I was afraid I wasn't going to bag. All I needed was Vanessa's hot tub, 3 beers, a gyro sandwich, j in the b, and a netflix and chill with Davey to send. Very nice climb.

ascents.name: Tied to the whipping post
ascents.comment: m-flash. so easy. for some reason yesterday I got to the V2 move and just could not pull at all. wow. I don't even think I know my body anymore. need to figure out how to rest effectively without getting fat.

ascents.name: Red Dragon
ascents.comment: On that body I could build a house

ascents.name: Monkey Bar Right
ascents.comment: It's a earthquake everytime your booty bounce! Damnnnnnn...

ascents.name: Mystic Rhythms
ascents.comment: A nice consolation prize after exploding my knee on Left Hand. In the paraphrased words of Dan Beall, 'I just don't know what I have to do to do this god damn boulder.' At least I will always have this on David.

ascents.name: Cave Route
ascents.comment: This is the hardest six i've done in the milks. went left hand to big sidepull jug with right hand on a small gaston. felt heinous but i really don't like doing that big move. classic gym baby problem.

ascents.name: Center Visor
ascents.comment: msoft second go no foot cut i ain't no bitch. Sorry Ak and DJ, this had to be done today. I can't wait forever.

ascents.name: Ruination
ascents.comment: it was hot as Denny's plates today and still fraished. I would say that I'm turning a new leaf  but this lip traverse is all crimping. and actually pretty fun. sit seems rough nuggets. undercling + fat ass is no bueno.

ascents.name: Black Moth Super Rainbow
ascents.comment: so ez. except not really actually. weird tension moves on holds all facing the same way. Good thing I'm not a big fat guy or this would have been reeeally difficult.

ascents.name: Can Opener Right
ascents.comment: Left hand good sidepull crimp, right hand really shitty knob, then bump to good crimp knob thing. Felt pretty hard in the heat but I ain't no Wendy Weaksauce.

ascents.name: Stemming Matters
ascents.comment:
anywhere from 4 to 6 depen-- nope not falling for that old trick again. Questioning my ability to pull these given i was climbing in cloth gloves the whole time.

A very wise man once said "bad bitch look good in some nice pants. Bet my bitch look good in some NICE PANTS!'think about it.

ascents.name: Tojo Risen
ascents.comment: the classic felt impossible til send then felt soft aka fitstfs. Pretty unique pinch block and nice moves. the feature! the Feature! top was kinda meh but whatevs.

ascents.name: Consumption Junction
ascents.comment: would have flashed but went to wrong hold then fell straight on the rock with my assbone. with two fat holes in my fingers i'm really teeing myself up for Colorado.

ascents.name: Captain's Junk
ascents.comment: kind of super uncomfortable and was the second to last thing I did this weekend. So gassed. can't believe i have to come back for Dreamtigerlowv7.

ascents.name: Courier Flight
ascents.comment: very tight. mflash. it's been called the deadbug of v6. but now that deadbug is v6....oh. deadbug is the deadbug of v6

ascents.name: *Dream Tiger
ascents.comment: def worth doing. bottom moves are like V4/5. matching sloper was hard for me. i can't even say that i'm a one-dimensional climber because not even soft jug sloper moves are easy for me. so psyched to bring a spade and porto-jackhammer to make the low start even softer.

ascents.name: Moondrops
ascents.comment: Shirley is making her way back to full strength. one softy at a time. also, Natebro pulled this piece after not climbing for two years. so pitted. tsee-yah

ascents.name: Way too High sit
ascents.comment: after i did the stand, i said i wouldn't do the sit. but then did it on the quick after david did the sit without doing the stand first. logbook no score and i'm reaping all the benefits.

ascents.name: Hugs For Gumby
ascents.comment: 2nd Ascent. A nice refrigerator bloc with an involved and full value mantel. Can't wait to go head to head  for the FA of Lilbehezie with Davey

ascents.name: Flight of Osirus
ascents.comment: so psyched all that touchstone training is paying off outdoors. classic kneebarz.

ascents.name: Power Windows
ascents.comment: Shirley swoops in with that good beta for Ak and Abuella. They both send next burn, leaving me to break the send train. took a few goes but I got there. This is a really bad boulder problem but at least fortune would have it my way. Someone stuffed 79 dollars into the bucket crimp. Thanks!

ascents.name: Tuna Juice
ascents.comment:
Shirley and Davey comeback tour 2017. Then Zev comes in and condescendingly kisses us with his gross beard after campusing the whole thing and skipping moves. and I'm not talking about our faces...



...i'm talking about our assholes.

ascents.name: Unnamed
ascents.comment: my asshole. i just separated my asshole.short but sweet.

ascents.name: Buddha Belly
ascents.comment: pretty unenjoyable. also thanks tram guidebook a la the start holds on greenpeace stand. troll.

ascents.name: Slot Machine
ascents.comment: I think we all experienced our own ballets today. A ballet of feelings. Emotions.

ascents.name: Butterscotch
ascents.comment: Did a hold break? Felt like solid 7A+ to me. Also this thing is pretty darn amazing. topout is ez just need to be short and/or have good hip flexibility. Awesome climb though. more people should do this.

ascents.name: Year of the Cat stand
ascents.comment:
Girl I respect the cat.

But not really. this climb sucks. This one took me more burns than everything else today. Yah yah. Yah yah. Yah Yah...

ascents.name: Skye Dance
ascents.comment:
I feel like that hike was crazy.
Feel like Druid Stones nothing short of amazing.
Feeling like fifty off of focaccia.
I feel like pot pie-- til the pot pie betrays me.

ascents.name: Sunshine Daydream
ascents.comment:
super fun. my style through and through. Sorry, Ak. If good ass intro moves into tier 1, maybe i'll consider giving this 7A+.

Edit 5/6/17 Wow I didn't think you'd actually do it. Well i'm a man of my word, Akhil and after careful consideration...

ascents.name: Trailside Arete
ascents.comment: Cool boulder. really enjoyed the two dudes who were bickering at each other over beta. Then one of puts a toehook in and does the move and the other says 'you had..a toehook in..this whole time?' 'yeah. it's the beta.' 'i'm gonna kill you.' this actually didn't happen but wouldn't be surprised if it did.

ascents.name: Nicole overhang
ascents.comment:
Dude wtf David this thing was not fucking easy. Probably would have helped if I wasn't starting one move lower than the actual start, but still felt not soft. Split both index fingers on the send go.

Another AK zinger: some guy was trying the sit start and was wondering if it would be an FA, but explained it probably wouldn't be because it's a fairly obvious line. He sends, everyone says nice job man except Akhil who just leads with 'What are you gonna name it?' hahahaha.

ascents.name: Meadows Direct
ascents.comment: not-soft second go from start after sussing (aka nssgfsas). can't wait to nssgfsas more climbs in the the future. topping out this entire boulder is hard at the end of the day.

ascents.name: Mega Ghost
ascents.comment: 3rd go. Psyched to be climbing outside. ultimate frisbee sounds really appealing though.

ascents.name: SIN Variation
ascents.comment: Actually super fun. Epic'd it after destroying two more tips and failed. Went on a nice little stroll to watch David and a Zev type flail on shitty stuff. Came back and thought 'fuck it' I'll give it one more.' I then proceeded to scream on the final 3 moves That would have given Ryan's Chris Sharma dick-riding-ass a full chub. Flex.

ascents.name: Saigon
ascents.comment: One more off the masterlist. Sliced my finger open on stained geezy. Skin is in defcon 5

ascents.name: Erotic Terrorist
ascents.comment: Bombed up from so cal around 1, straight to sads, Slimb, Andrew and I crushed this (with Scott's support) and left. Efficiency will hopefully remain the the theme on this trip. Dab

ascents.name: Drone Militia
ascents.comment: 3rd go. Wow this thing is fucking rad. Has my absolute favorite move in it with a high foot, big lock off to the joog crimps. psyched on this thing.

ascents.name: Rio's Crack
ascents.comment: I spoke with Rio and after explaining Ryan's situation, i was able to convince him to change the name to the Ryan Bauer Memorial Crack Problem. This thing classically felt really hard until i did it.

ascents.name: Every Color You Are
ascents.comment: so close to fraish then took 3 more goes after.unique holds and moves. #matthiaswhoelse led the send train and apparently everyone but the people's champion did it. but he's such a sweet boy!

ascents.name: The Diamond Left
ascents.comment: m-flashed after phonebooking the full line.

ascents.name: Seven Spanish Angels
ascents.comment: And finally the epic comes to an end. Hit the jug, dangled there for a little while, then realized i wasn't on the ground and actually said, in classic me, nonchalant-monotone style "Oh shit, I did it" then topped out. Felt so hard every other session. M-flashed on a warm day though...soft. just kidding.

ascents.name: Atari
ascents.comment: Finally mustered up the courage to throw the heel. Glad to have done this classic. It was 80 degrees and  the whole right arete was baking in the sun. Even David took a while to repeat this. Gotta be soft.

ascents.name: It's All About Love More Obvious and Less Stupid C
ascents.comment: hrmm..one move into the sit start apparently. sit start is the stupidest thing i've ever seen though so. there's that.

ascents.name: Prince of Thieves
ascents.comment: Holy isht. Did not think I would flash this one. This one played to my strengths well and still seemed really hard.Sandbox rolled strong this weekend.

ascents.name: Kauk Problem Sit
ascents.comment: Doesn't add much to the stand. But the stand is pretty fucking hard so there's that. Alas, this is still soft. Also lost my phone at the boulders. Fuck me.

ascents.name: Year of the Cockroach
ascents.comment: For whatever reason I just hate this kind of climbing. Send trained with your boy ODBS. Angry Shirley made a brief guest appearance hahaha. Only in Tramway.

ascents.name: Scary Monsters
ascents.comment: This thing is good fun. Pumpy ass first half to sweet crimping to an airy topout. Shoutout davey for beint such a strong donger

ascents.name: Pilot Light
ascents.comment:
Felt hard at the end of a good day. Completely dark, no headlamp for the top. Kelsey ran up the back, forgot her headlamp. Davey threw it over me as I hit the lip, almost clocks me in the back of the head. Once Kelsey grabs it I'm already topping out better than Ryan ever could!!

Edit: Topout was super casual with good beta. Right hand gaston, flip left hand to push press, step up, call it soft.

ascents.name: Low tide
ascents.comment:
So fucking hard. Basically ended my climbing day and it was the first thing I tried. Left bicep is so done. Cool lip traverse.

Edit: Went back to this boulder a few days later after the rain so jqee could send but it looks like someone broke the crimp one crosses to.

ascents.name: Change of heart
ascents.comment: Would have flashed if I knew where the correct fucking holds were. But alas, a nice 1,2,3 send train with your boys Dirk and Davey leading the charge.  Shoutout Ryan for the first of his two epic fluke sends.

ascents.name: Crossroads moe
ascents.comment: always a good time when you come back to a boulder that felt heinously hard before, and then just feels hard. But like a soft hard. Like LHTF. Bonus: climbed it way easier than Davey

ascents.name: WoodYard arete
ascents.comment: Holy isht. Excellent. Soft compression climbing on soft holds. Really soft. Don't think its good. Wait switch good and soft.

ascents.name: Black Plague
ascents.comment: Really good. Really should have flashed

ascents.name: The Hulk
ascents.comment: couldn't do the cross move last season. don't know if i got stronger or this got softer.

ascents.name: Atlantis
ascents.comment: so hard

ascents.name: G23 Arete
ascents.comment: Entertaining. good crimp compression up the face. curious to know how it got the name..cause I don't get it.

ascents.name: Solar power
ascents.comment: Awesome moves on a unique erratic boulder. Felt so hard, then the sun went down and it felt doable. soft.

ascents.name: Pflancake
ascents.comment: Supposed to be V8. But i cant in good faith take it. this problem kind of encompasses my feelings on sb south currently. Heinously soft, but so lovable.

ascents.name: Mashed Potatoes and Gravy
ascents.comment: Probably no harder than V4, but headiness plays a factor. Cool holds fun moves. and you get pretty high off the deck. Went full Chris Hoss mode on sunday and flailed on a boulder I had no business being on. Starting to get really psyched on the valley, namely Conan. Maybe I'll see Chris there, but he'll probably just be showing his OA homies all the boulders that Shirley will do before him while leading a yankee doodle sing along.

ascents.name: Ian's Prow
ascents.comment: Sick holds, sick moves. jqee with the improbable send. SB north is the new movement.

ascents.name: Tiger stripes
ascents.comment: Easier than Kneebar and The Kind. But is my style. It seems that crimps get higher grades around here.

ascents.name: Kneebar
ascents.comment:
Super-muffed the flash...

...damnit.

ascents.name: V6
ascents.comment: hand heel beta swaaaaaaagg!

ascents.name: Medusa
ascents.comment: This thing is pretty cool. angry chase made a guest appearance, which hasn't been seen since Jack of all tradesv4. flipped that meathook the other way and it went, but heel hooks were not on point today.

ascents.name: Only The Good Die Young
ascents.comment: dude this thing was sick! minimal jbs, good beta makes it v4-v5? whatever. mfrash is sack

ascents.name: Fists of Fury
ascents.comment: Man I thought wednesday was for real, but today we went uber ham. a true fitness day if you will. the send to flail ratio was much lower today, but the fitness was much more full value than say, a basic bitch trail. We went way the f down, then went way the f up.

ascents.name: Greasefire
ascents.comment: bagged it 3rd go. Fitness day slowly but oh so shirley turned into send day...usually you pay double for that kind of action cotton.

ascents.name: Red Spark
ascents.comment: my style through and through. took a handful of goes to stick the first move crux, the rest is V1. I was a fan of the move.

ascents.name: Mr. Witty
ascents.comment: Scooter was right. This thing is actually really sick!

ascents.name: NRA
ascents.comment: definitely not V7. Center visor feels harder. did the knee bar beta.

ascents.name: Chips
ascents.comment: Solid V6 imo, but a couple of really cool moves including a bicycle that isn't a bicycle but actually is. and a pogo a gogo to a jug.

ascents.name: Wills of Fire
ascents.comment: Epic'd this testpiece last year at a buck 80 and had my heart broken after hitting the jug rail. This year cruised it 1st go 10 lbs lighter. Amazing boulder. Perfectly my style. tsee-yah!

ascents.name: Munchkin Lunge
ascents.comment: awkward one move wonder DP with a heel hook. definitely short person friendly. the mantle was fun despite being 6 feet off the ground.

ascents.name: Bowling Pin Sit Start
ascents.comment: heinous first move but the full line is so cool. Doing rubber tester before this definitely made the topout super caj-wall, tsee-yah!

ascents.name: Jean Claude Van Damme (JCVD)
ascents.comment: Dude sick boulder. Glad we were able to find this thing. Put it down in a sesh as my first 6, so it's soft.

ascents.name: Bachar Problem Left
ascents.comment: Winnie pulled before Shirley. We may have done some p crazy v6+ beta

ascents.name: Bachar Problem Right
ascents.comment: These boulders are quite weird and glassy and sharp. but still good man. still good

ascents.name: The Huck
ascents.comment: ok guys here's the thing. this thing is extremely difficult. I don't understand it still. it was total limit for me

ascents.name: Umpa Lumpa
ascents.comment: Fun and funny. total limit for me. harder than monkey bar traverse

ascents.name: *The Pearl
ascents.comment: m-flash babyyy. might even be a soft second go idk how many times i tried it 3 years ago. The geezer flashed, the greaser couldn't do it all. what a day

ascents.name: The Crack Direct
ascents.comment: I didn't do a sit but maybe it is broken? people say this is v5 still. whatever. for the days climbed metric

ascents.name: Hyperglide
ascents.comment: God almighty the valley of despair continues. One week of rest is apparently not enough. My muscles are perpetually tired and achy and have been for the last couple of months. Perhaps two weeks off will reset everything so that I'm not miserable as soon as I pull onto the rock

ascents.name: Cocaine Biceps
ascents.comment: so dumpy. But the pointz were needed!

ascents.name: We Call Them Lines
ascents.comment: This is the eliminate on the warm up boulder. It is very important to call these sorts of things lines. It is equally important to describe, in perfect detail, how said lines are to be climbed. Thus this line goes as follows:

ascents.name: Preservation
ascents.comment: ehh. Cool looking but moves not so well. What a day in SD. Beers, enchiladas, steak, robots taking our jobs. Outrageous fun!

ascents.name: Christine Keeler
ascents.comment: m-soft second GO! Had to stay warm and loose for the spotting burns

ascents.name: Dragon Flake
ascents.comment: Wow that bottom was difficult. I think V5 is fair here. plus this contributes to my softness ranking on david.vaskos.com so it's a real win-win. Akhil didn't want to try because he's not quite sure he wants to flash V5 just yet, which is understandable from a rock climbing perspective.

ascents.name: Off the Couch
ascents.comment: Started with a couple of stacked pads. First move is hard but not really that hard. Osama feels about 2 grades harder

ascents.name: Superbump
ascents.comment: Aptly named as I did no bumping at all. Did it the hard way according to Kody after he made me blow the flash. A nice rock climb

ascents.name: Rhomboid
ascents.comment: Only took 35 more burns than Crimp Overhang must be soft! Wow what a nice rock climb. A must do for the area

ascents.name: El Diablo
ascents.comment: At long last a multi-year project goes down. This was the only boulder I could mustard myself upward in hot heat. Wow summer is by far the worst seasoning when sprinkled in with doing a bouldering

ascents.name: The Toy Climb
ascents.comment: just like Kody said, this climb is almost good. thought it was about 4/5 so i'll take the 5 and call it soft. David have you ever been to this area??

ascents.name: Footless traverse
ascents.comment: two stars for the holds at the end. such nice rock.

ascents.name: The Undercling
ascents.comment: oh wait i definitely did this one. what the hell is the hole?

ascents.name: Serengeti
ascents.comment: M flash after 4 years of avoiding it. So nice to fill this sea of green gap. What a wild ride!

ascents.name: Serengeti Right Variation
ascents.comment: lovely. this still counts right? i needs points bad booboo.

ascents.name: Newton's Law
ascents.comment: every hold feels like absolutely nothing but you just trust in the based god and somehow don't fall ever. sit looks impossible like wtf

ascents.name: High Noon
ascents.comment: m soft second go is the best. Especially when you say it as you're topping out and other people are like ...wtf? took about 4 sessions of not trying the move and wussing out to try it once and it didn't disappoint. hand foot match and lock off to lip classic me. mantle was ez.

ascents.name: Arbor Day
ascents.comment: very nice rock climb. no idea why I did what I did at the top but still managed to bag the flash! so weird to just actually suck so badly in the gym and still be able to pull decently well outside. i'm not complaining.

ascents.name: The Falcon
ascents.comment: ehh it's fine. 2 stars for heel pendulum move.

ascents.name: High Chaparral
ascents.comment: very cool. Marina led the way by finding the invisible crimp and I followed up after.

ascents.name: Devoted traverse
ascents.comment: boulders getting downgraded left and roight like a toiger i loive it! kinda hard, nice little boulder.

ascents.name: Shelter From the Storm
ascents.comment: very dumb rock climbing. what a waste of a name. still a pretty entertaining sequence. a touchstone climber's dream come true

ascents.name: Mr. Happy
ascents.comment: eh cool couple of moves. nice to stay on the rim and avoid most crowds today.

ascents.name: Captain Hook
ascents.comment: wtf this thing is kinda fucked for 5. hell it'd be kinda fucked for 6.

ascents.name: The Fang (sit)
ascents.comment: i find it funny that whoever first logged this climb on 8a put parentheses around 'sit.' As if adding the word sit was not enough to distinguish it from the non-sit. Sad to say that i did not soft second go after doing the stand but so it goes.

ascents.name: Unknown
ascents.comment: To the left of Big Present. So difficult. So scary. 1/10 would not do again.

ascents.name: Ok Problem Direct
ascents.comment: Off route all jugs grab that nipple, posture, and bump big baby! do if bored, otherwise nah.

ascents.name: Right Gold Crack
ascents.comment: this thing moves pretty terribly. I hate when all holds face the same way. Fell upwards on the last few moves. thank god for that mantel or I would have pumped out and died.

ascents.name: The Groveler
ascents.comment: Just saw that David has not done Chadinator. It seems you still have much to do here, Davey.

ascents.name: Rosie Palms
ascents.comment: started like idk one hand lower so i could get the foot on the og hand start. felt easy. swag

ascents.name: Imperfect Circle
ascents.comment: got the most insane sugar high after not eating all day and then eating a clif bar and decided to use this energy to rack up more points. this climb is meh. 1.5 stars for the points you can take.

ascents.name: Zun Factor
ascents.comment: ez. scott didn't flash. haha

ascents.name: Notta talus cave
ascents.comment: little dabby but nice climb overall. Good to come back and watch the sandbox gangbang it per usual.

ascents.name: Boulder Basin Dyno
ascents.comment: So hot. no flash. not even a soft second go. fun.

ascents.name: Groundwater
ascents.comment: Actually pretty nice moves for a lowball pockety shartpile. Some buca ex was trying to spray me his softy beta and never realized he was describing the V0 next to it.

ascents.name: The Vulcan Traverse
ascents.comment: 3 goes. psh. as if I could even think about doing a 4th one. So tired. David didn't think I could bag. Well I did David and you are now all the wiser because of it. Let it be known that I can do more than 6 moves on a boulder problem. V5 or less. I shall reap my rewards. I will rise again my sons. Alan will be  no more. Patience.

ascents.name: Crystal ball
ascents.comment: Got to last move on flash go with two napkins and no spots and forgot about a key hold and dropped a long way. Nice problem.

ascents.name: Masters of Reality
ascents.comment: Took a real long time to actually figure out how to hold that sloper. once I did though it was, as you can imagine, soft.

ascents.name: Ticket to Venus
ascents.comment: Knowing full well that Scooter '6AM PGSV Sesh' Limb flashed this gave my left quad the strength to do a straight up one-legged squat when hope was dimmest. Thank you Scoot. Thank you.

ascents.name: Pain Grain
ascents.comment: M-soft second go haven't done that in a while. So sharp. So hot. nice boulder. Top is just I don't know. My hand touches different holds everytime.

ascents.name: Leary/Bard arete
ascents.comment: When parked at the trailhead that leads to the buttermilker, make sure to not take that trail and instead walk the road all the way to birthday direct trailhead and then up to ironman traverse  then back down to this. Drew is a real visionary for these sorts of things and without his innovative approach i might not have flashed.

ascents.name: Kelvin and Hops
ascents.comment:
To the right of Mr. Fahrenheit. Jump start to a downward angled pinch block at the lip and find a way to pull on to the easy slab. Not sure if already done but It can't have a sicker name than this so I'll take it. One pad, a pair of cruzers, and an IPA is all you need.

Edit: Kelvin and Hops is apparently also the name of an IPA from Pizza Port Brewing. I don't know who is naming beers over there but kudos.

ascents.name: Freedom fighter
ascents.comment: Very nice boulder problem on some real sweet grips!! took a while due to bakes in the sun but once it went it was soft.

ascents.name: The Muffler
ascents.comment: Pretty sure this is the thing with the knee bars. In that case 3 stars for knee bars. In other news, this thing felt really fucked up for 6C. But also I think this was the worst I've ever felt on a trip ever and this was day 1. My body is dying.

ascents.name: Flying Festoon
ascents.comment: So fat. didn't eat or drink anything the whole day until David cracked open a 395 IPA for me. Sufficiently drunk, I felt the need to save the day by climbing something harder than V4 and locked in on this testpiece. This climb is tall, really really dirty, and is not over at the top. Also this climb is super dirty. In retrospect, had I not been decently inebriated, I would not have even bothered. But there's a really sick knee bar at the top that allows you to rest, contemplate life, wait for Drew to run up the back with chalk, have a nice conversation, then execute. If this was not dirty and friable it would be pretty sof--i mean good.

ascents.name: The Cuckoo's Nest
ascents.comment: Finally something that I did that David could also do. This thing is soft and a nice one mover with a cool xeno. 1.5 stars.

ascents.name: Where Boneheads Dare
ascents.comment: straight up improv sesh at the top. was I holding holds? i don't know. Maybe in an alternate universe I ate shit and died but glad I visited this one! Maybe, @crispychen, in an alternate universe, I took my shirt off and hard-man-hiked it with no pads. how bou dah?

ascents.name: Pineapple Express
ascents.comment: Nice moves on good rock. Kinda lowball and climb out of hole esque but that's Colorado. Wish I flashed but with 3  fingers with holes in them, i'll take the ssg. Apparently this is the farthest drive and it was only 2.5 hours. Someday, SB Colorado will be the new movement.

ascents.name: *Standard Bulge
ascents.comment: I'll show you a standard bulge. First boulder of the day and blew 3 tips simultaneously. Used to only get vag splits but somehow, things done changed8A+. No worries though because Colorado is beautiful and Fanny's Avery pro card helps me forget about them every night.

ascents.name: Tour de France Arete
ascents.comment: It has been so long since i've done a boulder problem that I think i actually forgot how to top out completely. Almost blew it twice what the hell

ascents.name: Unknown
ascents.comment:
Max grade was V5 this weekend. Failed to even Reach a Peach from a standing position. Fingers are toast. I hate mean green. and i hate the heat. at least the rest of my life is going real well...



not

ascents.name: Lichen, No Likin'
ascents.comment: cool 2 mover from kody black mountain shutt. glad he had kyle to spray him horrible beta for my infected donger or he wouldn't have pulled. not as cool as master blaster for sure. but way to get the low hanging fruit KBMS.

ascents.name: Crack-O-Pop
ascents.comment: Not sure what move involved a heinous heel hook. Easily avoidable I guess. Also I realized that I left the guidebook in the car so. Didn't get nearly as much volume as I had hoped for. Oh well sea of green.

ascents.name: Organ Grinder
ascents.comment: Is this just the softest V2 in the world V5? Pretty sure I did this right. Sometimes when you solo trip, no one else can deny your words. And that is how my news goes insider says that the way you think you know what about the people who are not really only a real man and barnacle uncle of two weeks is going well on 3G.

ascents.name: The Persistence of Time
ascents.comment: Ak with the mini epic send. Muffed the flash for the soft second go points.

ascents.name: Methane
ascents.comment: and beer and popcorn and lit'l smokies and bacon and brownies and...

ascents.name: The Cube
ascents.comment: msoft second go. longest standing project at Tramway finally taken down. So psyched. Definitely at least my 5th session on it and almost fell twice on the send go. Then Sarah proceeded to crush it in my face shortly after. Would give hard 7A+ but sea of green. Also 69th V5 tseeyah!

ascents.name: Arch Drude
ascents.comment:
i feel like shakin' it up.
You feel like she be fakin' it bruh?
She sent climb 29 you think she makin' it up??
wake up--feel like y'all let her take home the cup.

ascents.name: Arch Drude Left
ascents.comment:
For the sake of a fuck.
Feel like I'm always teeing me up.
Feel like fire in my fingers always wakin' me up.
Feel like Finder's Fee is cake--one day i'll get to the top.

ascents.name: Hook line and sinker
ascents.comment:
I feel like the druids were rough.
Feel like Drew's fat ass really woulda had fun.
Feel like Vorpal isn't 8A+.
Feel like it's obvi a softy -- not even 7A Choss

ascents.name: Suspenders
ascents.comment:
Feel like i'm really right on the cusp.
Feel like my climbing's gettin' better almost 7C+.
Feel like eating 2 mcgriddles only paying 4 bucks.

Hol up.

I feel like 2 mcgreezy's wasn't enough......

DAMN.

ascents.name: The Knobs
ascents.comment: M-flash. forgot i did this. tsee-yah!!

ascents.name: Slot Machine
ascents.comment: kinda cool. except when you get over the lip and you have to climb 10 feet of sandy slab.

ascents.name: JBMFP
ascents.comment: m-flash. wow so easy compared to high noon. wtf even is climbing anymore? Shoutout Sarah for sending the proj!

ascents.name: Yabba Dabba Don't Extension
ascents.comment: From the lowest part of the seam. Only did it just in case it was the actual start to yabba dabba don't. felt like heinous v5.

ascents.name: Intruder
ascents.comment: Blew flash by trying dumb beta first. Excellent movement. Too bad it's short and dabby. feels really nice to be outside and climbing again.

ascents.name: Anti Hero
ascents.comment: 3 stars for the knee bars. -1 star for the thumb catch I broke. Don't worry though it's still soft.

ascents.name: Sucker Punch
ascents.comment: Coming back to this after losing 20 lbs, this still felt ridiculously hard. Jeebus.

ascents.name: Blue Suede Shoes
ascents.comment: did i actually do it? no idea. is it soft? Well, you say tomato tomato I say tomato tomato

ascents.name: Chizam
ascents.comment: Decently fun moves on cool holds. Homer's long standing project goes down! Holy isht it was fucking hot here.

ascents.name: Fueled By Hate
ascents.comment:
This thing was kinda fucked up. definitely could be V6 but also who cares because this climb is pretty poopy.

Edit: apparently I did the sit start which is why it felt so fucked up. Luckily, I unknowingly did the stand start just so I wouldn't chuff the top. Holy soft

ascents.name: Rave Stand
ascents.comment: oh my god actually fuck this problem. Definitely redlined it at this point. I barely pulled this one out of my ass. Sit will get negative stars. calling it soft because fuck rave that's why.

ascents.name: And The Livin's Easy
ascents.comment: swag

ascents.name: Heavy Artillery Stand
ascents.comment: Giant move felt pretty hard. Pretty comparable in difficulty to hand grenade. Dabbed the first time I did it, so ran it back clean to make sure it was lost, but not forgotten.

ascents.name: Unnamed
ascents.comment: Compression session with Rydawg. Today was a day in which punting certainly was winning. Punted off little wing proper. Punted off this for soft second go, chased an antelope around for 88 miles only to find a woolly mammoth had run it over and a saber tooth tiger eating it. Wow, talk about bad luck huh? At least my new keurig comes in the mail in 3 days. I ordered it on costco's website, hope I don't get my identity stolen. There goes my 10 minute ergo break, better get back to the grind of risk assessment.

ascents.name: Unnamed Dyno
