ascents.comment: Figured out that I just can't dyno. Classic me to find an absurdly high foot to skip the dyno altogether. Honestly felt at least V6 this way. But when you're part of the sandbox, you ain't no bitch. Except Chris. He's a fat bitch. I know it's  hard to stress certain words via text, but try to stress the word 'fat' when you read this again. Oh what the hell, go ahead and stress 'bitch' too. You guys get it.

ascents.name: Kauk Problem
ascents.comment: Shoutout Dust for pulling the antistyle. This thing was hard. Harder than vaporized8a for sure. Alan--I mean Chris Hoss def can't do this then.

ascents.name: Black Matter
ascents.comment: So soft. Wish I could say I flash V6 but there is just no way. Good moves on comfy holds.

ascents.name: Central Scrutinizer Direct
ascents.comment: This thing was actually fucked up. Topout is really fucking hard. Def deserves the UG but alas, I ain't no bitch. Seems like a rare opportunity Shirley!

ascents.name: The Bubble
ascents.comment: Took a while to figure out that skipping everything but jugs is the only way to make boulders soft.

ascents.name: Flying Birdie
ascents.comment: Cool climb. start jug was quite moist. gotta come back for the sitter. Can't believe I have haul my fat ass back up to the pimp juice boulder. But alas, sometimes punting is winning.

ascents.name: Unnamed
ascents.comment: I'm guessing this is that compression thing. Actually pretty darn cool. certainly not easy. soft.

ascents.name: Walrus
ascents.comment: Wtf. This thing sucks.

ascents.name: Boneslinger
ascents.comment: Link up starting on sling blade doing a couple cool shoulder moves into dem bones. Im super positive someone has done this because its so soft but i feel ready to make my mark on joes valley.

ascents.name: Rug Right
ascents.comment: Cool feature. Most sandbagged boulder in Joe's. Smoothie, this, and that other thing. Holy shit.

ascents.name: Smoothie
ascents.comment: Really cool climb. Have to go back for the proper start. Footshelf not on thanks for making sure we knew that E-rok!

ascents.name: Pimpers Paradise
ascents.comment: Wanted to do Scott's pogo beta, but just wanted the soft flash points more. Shoutout fryable chossy freesolo on the frontside of this boulder. The whole sandbox went up it and no one died. Hooray!

ascents.name: Maxipad
ascents.comment: Slam dunk feels super hard when youre 5'8". Such a fun climb. Tsee-yah! Also shoutout fingers. Two holes in my indices i cry witcha.

ascents.name: Go Granny Go Right
ascents.comment: 3rd go had to warm up fingers on first two burns. Closes the book on go granny. Good movement  butnot as much athleticism needed as for go granny go, so it must be soft. Also lol at David. One for taking a job somewhere that isn't the bay, and two, for being worried that her royal girthiness was stronger than him. I'm coming for you David, one soft crimpy climb at a time.

ascents.name: Sunshine
ascents.comment: This thing was kinda fucked up. Violent compression.

ascents.name: Atlas
ascents.comment: Giving this the recommend for the sickness quality. one ginormous move. Feet cut, heinous swing. this is rock climbing. soft

ascents.name: Silent Spotter
ascents.comment: holy soft. really good movement. classic ucla rockwall set. having said that you can lick lick lick lick my balls sandbox south..yeah! say that shit all the time!

ascents.name: Rene
ascents.comment: I'll give it one star with the only redeeming quality being that I never have to go back to this boulder ever again. find a new spotter jacquie.

ascents.name: Go Granny Go
ascents.comment: full value jump beta. you straight won't ryan.

ascents.name: Molly
ascents.comment: A slightly better, slightly harder version of solarium. which isn't saying much because solarium is a choss pile. cool jump move.

ascents.name: Strength in Numbers
ascents.comment: super classic. ran it back 2.9 times for fitness. psyched to do this thing.

ascents.name: Cocaine corner
ascents.comment: felt impossible last time. davey came through with good beta. Amazing arete climbing with tenuous feet.

ascents.name: Jedi Jake Stand
ascents.comment: this thing is so fun! surprised on the flash. cool moves and features. Good boulder.

ascents.name: Hueco Wall
ascents.comment: such subtle. so bump. three times. wow. soft

ascents.name: Cellulite Eliminator
ascents.comment: (the stand) Felt hardish to me. but i'm fat and weak so there is that. super awesome climb. the 8 year old girl who walked up it gave me the motivation to flail more.

ascents.name: Hydroponics
ascents.comment: This thing was good fun. stoffie, jqueezy and your boy were all atop the boulder having no idea where/how to downclimb. classic.

ascents.name: Facemeat Dyno
ascents.comment: holy isht. this thing is super fun. like summer 2015 rockwall fun.

ascents.name: The Kind
ascents.comment: Not my style. awesome moves but wanted me some crimps! I have to stop warming up on pumpyass V5's

ascents.name: V5 - The Cube Boulder
ascents.comment: holy soft. first 6C flash eva! huge ass holds

ascents.name: Autobot
ascents.comment: Bottom was cool despite the good, but less than ideal crimps and weird moves off of them. but the top is just glory. Scared of the fall into the dangit hole until i pulled off the ground. then i didn't think about it at all.

ascents.name: Deep Puddle Arete
ascents.comment: would have flashed if it wasn't for the fact that this was the first boulder I got on here at lower chos. pumped the rest of the day

ascents.name: Unnamed?
ascents.comment: opposite that one v10. probably V4, but this trip makes you read the story a little different. swag. swag. swag. swag.

ascents.name: The Dali Stand
ascents.comment: perfect rock! awesome dyno. did all the moves to the full line but not steong enough to link. brain gotta poop...still

ascents.name: The Wave
ascents.comment: Did the double dyno from the start. Easier, more fun, and so much sicker than using the other holds. I Felt awful but the girth in me was strong! Shoutout slooomooo

ascents.name: Tooth Fairy
ascents.comment:
Nice movement down low to some weirdness up high. But like a good kinda weird. Like those times when shirley takes a hold of chases body and drones on for hours about not charging her hearing aid. Thing is pretty soft though. Maybe soft 5

edit: i think about this climb every so often and had to clear my conscience.

ascents.name: Obe Problem Right
ascents.comment: Blew the flash cause davey didnt spray me hard enough!

ascents.name: Crouching Tiger Hidden Dragon
